<h2 class="blog--title">
<a href="/blog/2009/10/21/dm-admin-console-demo-screencast">dm Admin Console Demo Screencast</a>
</h2>
<header class="meta-data--container">
<div class="meta-data--item desktop-only">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon engineering"></div>
<a class="category" href="/blog/category/engineering">Engineering</a>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<img class="meta-data--icon" src="https://gravatar.com/avatar/30994352b9a990d525f9aed9718b012a?s=20&amp;d=mm" />
<span class="author">Christopher Frost</span>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon calendar"></div>
<time class="date" pubdate="" datetime="2009-10-21 17:06:00.0">October 21, 2009</time>
</div>
<div class="meta-data--item">
<div class="meta-data--icon icon blog-icon comments"></div>
<a class="comments" data-disqus-identifier="276" href="/blog/2009/10/21/dm-admin-console-demo-screencast#disqus_thread">
</a></div>
</header>
<section class="blog--post desktop-only">
<div><p>Here is a screencast showing the <em>dm Admin Console</em> for the <em>dm Server</em>. It gives a brief tour of the <em>dm Admin Console</em> and then shows some of the features by deploying a simple demo application. The application consists of a configuration file, a web bundle and a content bundle. When deployed the application simply shows the contents of the configuration file in a web browser. The application is installed in parts for the purpose of this demo, in reality you would group the application together with either a ‘<em>par</em>’ or a ‘<em>plan</em>’, to see how this is done with a ‘<em>plan</em>’ file another screencast is available <a href="http://blog.springsource.com/2009/09/11/configuration-properties-screencast/">here</a>.</p>
</div>
